约翰逊支持伦敦的金融部门，并谴责[[2008年金融危机|2007-08年金融危机]]之后他所看到的“银行家受抨击”的现象，{{sfnm|1a1=Purnell|1y=2011|1p=400|2a1=Gimson|2y=2012|2p=324}}谴责2011年出现的[[反资本主义|反资本主义]]的{{le|占领伦敦运动|Occupy London}}。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|pp=439–440}}他花了很多时间与那些参与金融服务的人交往，并批评政府对高收入者的50%税率。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=400}}他组织富人慈善捐款，捐赠给市长基金，该基金是为帮助处境不利的青年而设立的；虽然最初宣布它将筹集1亿英镑，到2010年，它只筹到了150万英镑。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=414}}他还保留了在英国媒体广泛的人脉，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=389}}帮助新闻媒体对其市政厅正面报道。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=389}}反过来，他在[[世界新闻报|世界新闻报]][[世界新闻报电话窃听丑闻|电话窃听丑闻]]期间仍然支持他的媒体朋友，其中包括[[鲁伯特·默多克|鲁伯特·默多克]]。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|pp=424–425}}

2008年5月8日约翰逊宣布成立法务审计小组。小组的任务是监测和调查{{le|伦敦开发署|London Development Agency}}和[[大伦敦政府|大伦敦政府]]的财务管理。<ref name=lgovpr20080508>{{cite press release |title=Mayor of London announces new Forensic Audit Panel to investigate GLA and LDA |publisher=Greater London Authority |date=2008-05-08 |url=http://www.london.gov.uk/view_press_release.jsp?releaseid=16814 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080518065203/http://www.london.gov.uk/view_press_release.jsp?releaseid=16814 |archivedate=2008-05-18 |accessdate=2008-05-07 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>约翰逊的公告受到工党的批评，认为这个名义上的独立小组的实际上是政治化的，小组成员的任命必须过问约翰逊的意见，批评言论包括“真正目的直指前市长利文斯通”和“不当利用公共开支”。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mayorwatch.co.uk/Labour-Accuse-Mayor-of-Tory-Witch-Hunt-article_id-1616.html |title=Labour accuse Mayor of 'Tory witch hunt' |publisher=MayorWatch |date=2008-05-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513014713/http://www.mayorwatch.co.uk/Labour-Accuse-Mayor-of-Tory-Witch-Hunt-article_id-1616.html |accessdate=2013-09-12 |archivedate=2008-05-13 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>这个小组的负责人{{le|裴申思·惠特克罗夫特|Patience Wheatcroft, Baroness Wheatcroft}}与保守党议员结婚，<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/media/2006/jul/17/mediaguardiantop100200638 The Media Guardian 100 – 87 Patience Wheatcroft] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2006/jul/17/mediaguardiantop100200638 |date=20190608023333 }}. ''The Guardian'' (London). 17 July 2006.</ref>另外四名小组成员中有三名与保守党有密切联系：{{le|斯蒂芬·格林哈尔什|Stephen Greenhalgh}}（自治市保守党领袖）、<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conservativehome.com/tag/stephen-greenhalgh|title=Stephen Greenhalgh {{!}} Conservative Home|access-date=2016-06-25|archive-date=2019-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622121535/https://www.conservativehome.com/tag/stephen-greenhalgh|dead-url=no}}</ref>帕特里克·弗雷德里克（保守党东南英格兰和南伦敦商务关系主席）和爱德华·李斯特（自治市保守党领袖）。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.standard.co.uk/news/mayor/ken-livingstone-refuses-to-appear-before-lda-audit-panel-6863880.html |title=Ken Livingstone refuses to appear before LDA audit panel |date=2008-07-15 |work=London Evening Standard |access-date=2016-06-25 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062117/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/mayor/ken-livingstone-refuses-to-appear-before-lda-audit-panel-6863880.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[File:BorisOC2010.jpg|thumb]]
在他第一任期内，约翰逊卷入了几个私人丑闻。搬到伊斯灵顿的新家后，他在阳台上建了一个棚子，没有获得规划许可；邻居投诉后，他拆了棚子。{{sfnm|1a1=Purnell|1y=2011|1pp=396–397|2a1=Gimson|2y=2012|2p=308}}约翰逊还被指与名为海伦·麦金太尔的女士有婚外情和私生子，他未作否认。{{sfnm|1a1=Purnell|1y=2011|1pp=407–410|2a1=Gimson|2y=2012|2pp=330–331}}<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/dec/15/no-censure-boris-johnson-city-hall-adviser |location=London |work=The Guardian |first=Helene |last=Mulholland |title=No censure for Boris Johnson over relationship with unpaid City Hall adviser |date=2010-12-15 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2020-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202040258/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/dec/15/no-censure-boris-johnson-city-hall-adviser |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/jul/20/boris-johnson-mayor-2012-macintyre |location=London |work=The Guardian |first=Hélène |last=Mulholland |title=Boris Johnson pressed for full details of the appointment of his alleged lover |date=2010-07-20 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062215/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/jul/20/boris-johnson-mayor-2012-macintyre |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Telegraph210513">{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/10070055/Public-has-right-to-know-about-Boris-Johnsons-secret-lovechild-court-rules.html |title=Public has right to know about Boris Johnson's secret lovechild, court rules |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=2013-05-21 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062132/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/10070055/Public-has-right-to-know-about-Boris-Johnsons-secret-lovechild-court-rules.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>约翰逊还因提前警告保守党国会议员、大学学长[[达米安·格林|达米安·格林]]警察要逮捕他的消息而惹来争议；约翰逊否认了这种说法，没有根据《{{le|刑事司法法|Criminal Justice Act}}》面临刑事指控。{{sfnm|1a1=Purnell|1y=2011|1pp=380–385|2a1=Gimson|2y=2012|2pp=305–308}}他在人事上也被批[[任人唯亲|任人唯亲]]，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=407}}他任命了一位支持他的前标准晚报编辑{{le|韦罗妮卡·罗德利|Veronica Wadley}}为伦敦{{le|艺术委员会|Arts council}}主席，她被广泛认为不适任。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|pp=401–402}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2009/oct/09/boris-johnson-ken-livingstone-standard |title=Ken Livingstone claims Boris Johnson tried to 'pay off' former Evening Standard editor |work=The Guardian |date=2009-10-09 |last=Mulholland |first=Hélène |location=London |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062227/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2009/oct/09/boris-johnson-ken-livingstone-standard |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/politics/article6865287.ece |work=The Times |title=Boris Johnson 'broke rules' by proposing ally for top London arts job |date=2009-10-08 |first=Sam |last=Coates |location=London |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2011-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110430103550/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/politics/article6865287.ece |dead-url=no }}{{subscription required}}</ref>约翰逊也卷入了{{le|国会开支丑闻|United Kingdom parliamentary expenses scandal}}，他报销的出租车费用太多，与他的副市长伊恩·克莱门特被发现滥用市政府信用卡，克莱门特因此辞职。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|pp=392–395}}约翰逊在伦敦是受欢迎的人物，具有很强的名人地位。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=446}}2009年11月，他骑车遇见被三个反社会青年绑架的摄影师{{le|弗兰妮·阿姆斯特朗|Franny Armstrong}}并解救了她。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=308}}<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/london/8340865.stm |title=Johnson saves woman from 'oiks' |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2009-11-07 |date=2009-11-03 |archive-date=2020-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301104808/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/london/8340865.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1934572,00.html |title=London Mayor Boris Johnson Saves Filmmaker from Mugging |work=Time |location=New York |accessdate=2009-11-07 |date=2009-11-04 |archive-date=2013-08-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826210402/http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1934572,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[2012年|2012年]]约翰逊谋求连任大伦敦市长，他再次聘请{{le|林顿·克罗斯比|Lynton Crosby}}策划他的竞选活动。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=338}}在选举前，约翰逊出版了新书《约翰逊的伦敦生活》，这是一本受欢迎的历史作品，历史学家{{le|A·N·威尔逊|A. N. Wilson}}将其称为“催票密码本”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|pp=447–448}}民意调查显示，尽管利文斯通的交通政策更受欢迎，但伦敦的选民对约翰逊在犯罪和经济问题上的信任度更高。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=440}}在2012年市长选举期间，约翰逊面对卷土重来的工党候选人、前市长利文斯通。约翰逊的选举运动强调了利文斯通犯有[[逃税|逃税]]罪，而利文斯通称约翰逊是“赤裸裸的骗子”。{{sfn|Crines|2013|p=3}}政治学家安德鲁·克里尼斯（Andrew Crines）认为，利文斯通的竞选集中注意力于批评约翰逊，而不是对伦敦的未来提出替代和进步的政策愿景。{{sfn|Crines|2013|p=2}}2012年，约翰逊再次击败利文斯通当选大伦敦市长。<ref name=BBC5May12>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-17946742 |title=London mayor: Boris Johnson wins second term by tight margin 5 May 2012 Last updated at 01:35 |date=2012-05-05 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2012-05-05 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062157/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-17946742 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==== 第二届市长任期（2012年－2016年） ====
[[File:Boris_2012.jpg|thumb]]期间]]
伦敦成功地主办了[[2012年夏季奥运会|2012年夏季奥运会]]，而申奥成功的2005年是[[肯·利文斯通|肯·利文斯通]]市长任内。约翰逊在筹办中的作用是担任奥林匹克委员会的联席主席，负责监督奥运会。<ref>{{cite web |title=The Mayor of London – 2012 Olympics |url=http://www.london2012.com/about-us/the-people-delivering-the-games/stakeholders/the-mayor-of-london/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120729172513/http://www.london2012.com/about-us/the-people-delivering-the-games/stakeholders/the-mayor-of-london/ |publisher=London 2012 |accessdate=2012-12-11 |archivedate=2012-07-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在担任这个角色后，他的两个行动一是改善伦敦附近的交通，在繁忙和大量游客涌入的时候，加开更多的班次，并在首都附近开设更多的公共汽车线路；<ref>{{cite news |title=Boris Johnson on London 2012 Olympics tickets and transport |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/video/2012/jul/30/boris-johnson-olympics-tickets-transport-video |publisher=The Guardian (video) |accessdate=2012-12-11 |date=2012-07-30 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062207/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/video/2012/jul/30/boris-johnson-olympics-tickets-transport-video |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |publisher=BBC News |title=London 2012: Boris Johnson says capital is prepared |url=http://bbc.co.uk/news/uk-18944191 |accessdate=2012-12-11 |date=2012-07-22 |archive-date=2012-10-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121031135315/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-18944191 |dead-url=no }}</ref>二是允许商店和超市在星期日有更长的{{le|营业时间|Sunday shopping}}。<ref name="conservative home">{{cite web |last=Bozier |first=Luke |title=Boris should fight for London to be open on Sundays |date=2012-09-09 |url=http://conservativehome.blogs.com/platform/2012/09/luke-bozier.html |publisher=Conservative Home blogs |accessdate=2012-12-11 |archive-date=2012-11-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102091806/http://conservativehome.blogs.com/platform/2012/09/luke-bozier.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>然而约翰逊被指控在奥运会开幕之前通过部署除尘剂来除去监测站附近的空气颗粒物以掩盖污染。<ref name=tele/>2013年11月，约翰逊宣布对[[伦敦地铁|伦敦地铁]]的运营进行重大改革，包括延长运营时间，新开周末晚间班次。还宣布，所有地下售票处将关闭，目的是每年节省超过4000万英镑，而提供自动票务系统。<ref name=bbc_tube_ticket>{{cite news |title=Every Tube ticket office to close |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-25025888 |accessdate=2013-11-21 |publisher=BBC News |date=2013-11-21 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062019/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-25025888 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=es_shakeup>{{cite news |last=Beard |first=Matthew |title=950 London Underground staff to lose their jobs in Tube ticket office shake-up |url=http://www.standard.co.uk/news/transport/950-london-underground-staff-to-lose-their-jobs-in-tube-ticket-office-shakeup-8954060.html |accessdate=2013-11-21 |newspaper=London Evening Standard |date=2013-11-21 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062309/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/transport/950-london-underground-staff-to-lose-their-jobs-in-tube-ticket-office-shakeup-8954060.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[File:Boris_johnson_opens_CSGS_building_March_2016.jpg|thumb]]
