==== 市长遗产 ====
2016年5月7日，约翰逊卸任大伦敦市长。离任后，他仍然受到伦敦人民的欢迎。在其任期结束时委托舆观调查公司所做民意调查显示，52％的伦敦人认为他的市长做得“不错”，而只有29％认为他做得“糟糕”。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yougov.co.uk/news/2016/05/05/mayor-boris-public-verdict/|title=YouGov {{!}} Mayor Boris: the public verdict|website=YouGov: What the world thinks|access-date=2018-07-17|archive-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718234445/https://yougov.co.uk/news/2016/05/05/mayor-boris-public-verdict/|dead-url=no}}</ref>而其继任者[[萨迪克·汗|萨迪克·汗]]在同一项民意调查中只有31％的受访者认为他的表现会比约翰逊更好。

在2016年，他为大伦敦警察购买的三个德国制造的[[水炮|水炮]]，未等时任内政大臣[[特蕾莎·梅|特蕾莎·梅]]使用，就被繼任市長出售，资金用于青年服务。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jul/01/water-cannon-boris-johnson-sold-off-without-being-used |title=Water cannon bought by Boris Johnson to be sold off without being used |work=The Guardian |date=2016-07-01 |accessdate=2016-07-01 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206070040/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jul/01/water-cannon-boris-johnson-sold-off-without-being-used |dead-url=no }}</ref>

约翰逊可能因在市长任上的不当行为而被调查，原因是在建造泰晤士[[花园桥_(伦敦)|花园桥]]时花费了过多的资金。工党国会议员[[安德鲁·格恩|安德鲁·格恩]]说：“鲍里斯·约翰逊在他的市长期间内推动了这个项目，他需要就他和他的办公室在鲁莽决定支出公共资金用于施工合同中所起的作用提供答案。”<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/feb/28/boris-johnson-could-face-investigation-over-thames-garden-bridge Boris Johnson could face investigation over Thames garden bridge] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/feb/28/boris-johnson-could-face-investigation-over-thames-garden-bridge |date=20210206062443 }} ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]'' 28 February 2018</ref>2018年3月，《卫报》报道称对约翰逊的压力正在增加，并且对他试图的解释持怀疑态度。<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/mar/19/boris-johnson-under-growing-pressure-over-scrapped-garden-bridge Boris Johnson under growing pressure over scrapped garden bridge] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/mar/19/boris-johnson-under-growing-pressure-over-scrapped-garden-bridge |date=20210126151520 }} ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]'' 19 March 2018</ref>

=== 重返国会 ===
约翰逊最初否认他将回归下议院，而是将继续完成市长任期。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=446}}然而，经过多次媒体猜测，2014年8月，他成为保守党的安全席位[[堊橋及南雷士廉_(英國國會選區)|堊橋及南雷士廉]]选区的候选人，参加[[2015年英國大選|2015年英國大選]]，<ref>{{cite news |last=de Peyer |first=Robin |title=Boris Johnson declares he will stand in Uxbridge and South Ruislip |url=http://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson-declares-he-will-stand-in-uxbridge-and-south-ruislip-9691619.html |accessdate=2014-08-26 |work=London Evening Standard |date=2014-08-26 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062356/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson-declares-he-will-stand-in-uxbridge-and-south-ruislip-9691619.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>9月正式成为候选人。<ref>{{cite news |last=Johnston |first=Chris |title=Boris Johnson selected to stand for Tories in Uxbridge and South Ruislip |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/sep/12/boris-johnson-tory-candidate-uxbridge-south-ruislip |accessdate=2015-03-30 |work=The Guardian |location=London |date=2014-09-12 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062451/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/sep/12/boris-johnson-tory-candidate-uxbridge-south-ruislip |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Swinford, Steven; Holehouse, Matthew (12 September 2014). [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2015/11093857/Boris-Johnson-selected-to-stand-for-Tories-in-Uxbridge-and-South-Ruislip.html "Boris Johnson selected to stand for Tories in Uxbridge and South Ruislip"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2015/11093857/Boris-Johnson-selected-to-stand-for-Tories-in-Uxbridge-and-South-Ruislip.html |date=20210206062404 }}. ''The Daily Telegraph''. London. Retrieved 4 April 2015.</ref>2015年在5月7日英国举行大选，约翰逊再次當選[[英國下議院|英國下議院]]議員，人们猜测他返回下议院是想取代[[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]的[[英国首相|首相]]和[[保守黨领袖_(英國)|保守党领袖]]之位。<ref>{{cite news |last=Bennett |first=Asa |url=http://www.londonlovesbusiness.com/business-news/politics/boris-johnson-lacks-the-skills-to-be-prime-minister-says-tory-chairman/3431.article |title=Boris Johnson lacks the skills to be prime minister, says Tory chairman |publisher=LondonlovesBusiness.com |date=2012-09-17 |accessdate=2012-10-08 |archive-date=2012-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007233049/http://www.londonlovesbusiness.com/business-news/politics/boris-johnson-lacks-the-skills-to-be-prime-minister-says-tory-chairman/3431.article |dead-url=yes }}</ref>约翰逊亦受卡梅伦之邀列席内阁政治性会议。

==== 英国脱欧运动（2015年－2016年） ====
