约翰逊在2016年年初成为媒体关注的中心，他拒绝澄清对[[英國退出歐盟|英國退出歐盟]]的支持。2016年2月，他在“[[英國脫歐公投|英国脱欧公投]]”运动中赞成投票脱欧。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-35626621 |title=Boris Johnson says UK is better off outside the EU |date=2012-02-21 |accessdate=2012-02-21 |publisher=BBC News |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206064138/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-35626621 |dead-url=no }}</ref>他把卡梅伦的对脱欧的恐惧看成“非常夸张”。金融市场上，约翰逊宣布支持脱欧后[[英镑|英镑]]下跌了近2％，是自2009年3月以来的最低水平。<ref>{{cite news |last=Wearden |first=Graeme |title=Pound hits seven-year low after Boris Johnson's Brexit decision |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2016/feb/22/pound-falls-city-gets-brexit-jitters-business-live |accessdate=2016-02-22 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=2016-02-22 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062530/https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2016/feb/22/pound-falls-city-gets-brexit-jitters-business-live |dead-url=no }}</ref>当[[奥巴马|奥巴马]]敦促英国留在欧盟时，约翰逊说，总统是由他的[[肯尼亚|肯尼亚]]血统造成的反英情绪才引发如此言论的。<ref>{{cite news |last=Stone |first=Jon |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/barack-obama-hits-back-at-boris-johnson-and-explains-why-he-moved-winston-churchill-bust-in-the-oval-a6997026.html |title=Barack Obama hits back at Boris Johnson and explains why he moved Winston Churchill bust in the Oval Office |website=The Independent |location=London |date=2016-04-22 |accessdate=2016-06-30 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424074304/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/barack-obama-hits-back-at-boris-johnson-and-explains-why-he-moved-winston-churchill-bust-in-the-oval-a6997026.html |archivedate=2016-04-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref>这些评论被谴责为种族主义，被一些[[工党_(英国)|工党]]和[[自由民主党_(英国)|自由民主党]]政治人物所不能接受，<ref name="ObamaSmear">{{cite news |title=Obama hits back at Boris Johnson's alleged smears |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36112694 |accessdate=2016-04-23 |publisher=BBC News |date=2016-04-22 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062352/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36112694 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="ToIApril16">{{cite news |last1=Lawless |first1=Jill |title=London mayor under fire for 'loaded' criticism of 'part-Kenyan' Obama |url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/london-mayor-under-fire-for-loaded-criticism-of-part-kenyan-obama/ |accessdate=2016-04-23 |work=[[The_Times_of_Israel|The Times of Israel]] |location=Jerusalem |date=2016-04-22 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062443/https://www.timesofisrael.com/london-mayor-under-fire-for-loaded-criticism-of-part-kenyan-obama/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[伦敦国王学院|伦敦国王学院]]学生会因此取消了对他发表演讲的邀请。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/2016/04/25/boris-johnson-no-platformed-over-obamas-ancestry-comments/ |title=Boris Johnson 'no platformed' over Obama's ancestry comments |author=Espinoza, Javier |work=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |accessdate=2016-04-28 |date=2016-04-28 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062506/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/2016/04/25/boris-johnson-no-platformed-over-obamas-ancestry-comments/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>相反，他的评论由[[英国独立党|英国独立党]]（UKIP）领袖[[奈杰尔·法拉奇|奈杰尔·法拉奇]]和保守党前领袖[[伊恩·邓肯·史密斯|伊恩·邓肯·史密斯]]支持。<ref name="ObamaSmear" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/redbox/topic/the-europe-question/ids-defends-boris-obama-comments |title=Duncan Smith: "There's nothing worse than hurling a word like 'racist'" |date=2016-04-25 |work=Times Red Box |subscription=yes |last1=Clark |first1=Natasha |accessdate=2016-04-26 |archive-date=2016-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223013118/http://www.thetimes.co.uk/redbox/topic/the-europe-question/ids-defends-boris-obama-comments |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/live/2016/apr/25/eu-referendum-gove-boris-johnson-brexit-