2016年7月13日，随着[[文翠珊|文翠珊]]成为新一任[[英国首相|英国首相]]，约翰逊被任命为[[外交及聯邦事務大臣|外交及聯邦事務大臣]]。<ref name="BloombergFSec">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-07-13/boris-johnson-appointed-u-k-foreign-secretary-in-may-government|title=Boris Johnson Appointed U.K. Foreign Secretary in May Government|trans_title=约翰逊任梅内阁外交大臣|last=RobDotHutton|first=Robert Hutton|website=Bloomberg.com|access-date=2016-07-13|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108112547/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-07-13/boris-johnson-appointed-u-k-foreign-secretary-in-may-government|dead-url=no}}</ref>不过由于他以前发表过许多争议性的言论，因此该任命受到一些记者和政治人物的批评。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/jul/13/boris-johnson-diplomacy-not-synonymous|title=Boris Johnson and diplomacy are not synonymous|trans_title=鲍里斯·约翰逊和外交不是同义词|date=2016-07-13|accessdate=2016-07-14|newspaper=The Guardian|author=Patrick Wintour|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062640/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/jul/13/boris-johnson-diplomacy-not-synonymous|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="FSecReactions">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-36790977|title=Boris Johnson is foreign secretary: The world reacts|trans_title=约翰逊任外交大臣：世界反应|date=2016-07-14|accessdate=2016-07-14|publisher=BBC News|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062647/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-36790977|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="GuardianReactions">{{cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/jul/14/maybe-the-brits-are-just-having-us-on-the-world-reacts-to-boris-johnson-as-foreign-minister|title='Maybe the Brits are just having us on': the world reacts to Boris Johnson as foreign minister|trans_title=“也许英国人只是和我们开玩笑”：世界对外交大臣鲍里斯·约翰逊的反应|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2016-07-14|accessdate=2016-07-14|author=Bonnie Malkin|author2=Philip Oltermann|author3=Tom Phillips|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062651/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/jul/14/maybe-the-brits-are-just-having-us-on-the-world-reacts-to-boris-johnson-as-foreign-minister|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[瑞典首相|瑞典前首相]][[卡尔·比尔特|卡尔·比尔特]]说：“我希望这是一个笑话。”[[法國外交部|法国外交部长]][[让-马克·埃罗|让-马克·埃罗]]说：“我完全不担心鲍里斯·约翰逊，但是……在竞选期间他对英国人说了很多话，现在是他无路可退”因为英国试图与欧盟就其未来关系谈判。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-wrapup-idUSKCN0ZU1HE |last1=Holton |first1=Kate |last2=Pitas |first2=Costas |date=2016-07-14 |title=May builds new-look Brexit cabinet to steer EU divorce |website=Reuters |publisher=Thomson Reuters |access-date=2016-07-14 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062717/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-wrapup-idUSKCN0ZU1HE |dead-url=no }}</ref>相反，[[澳大利亚总理|澳大利亚前总理]][[托尼·阿博特|托尼·阿博特]]欢迎这次任命，称他为“澳大利亚的朋友”。<ref name="GuardianReactions"/>美国政府的高级官员称，约翰逊的任命将推动[[德美关系|美国与德国的进一步关系]]，牺牲与英国的[[英美关系|特殊关系]]。<ref name="ITV20160714">{{cite news |url=http://www.itv.com/news/2016-07-13/reaction-boris-johnson-foreign-secretary-united-states-of-america/ |title=Boris Johnson's appointment as Foreign Secretary has not gone down well in the United States |author=Robert Moore |date=2016-07-14 |accessdate=2016-07-14 |publisher=ITV News |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062700/https://www.itv.com/news/2016-07-13/reaction-boris-johnson-foreign-secretary-united-states-of-america |dead-url=no }}</ref>

一些分析家认为这项任命可能是梅在政治上削弱约翰逊的策略：新设立的[[退出欧洲联盟事务大臣|脱欧大臣]]和[[国际贸易大臣|国际贸易大臣]]这两个职务将削弱外交大臣的权力，<ref name="BloombergFSec"/><ref name="GoodForMay">{{cite news |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/staggers/2016/07/sending-boris-johnson-foreign-office-bad-britain-good-theresa-may |title=Sending Boris Johnson to the Foreign Office is bad for Britain, good for Theresa May |date=2016-07-14 |accessdate=2016-07-14 |author=Stephen Bush |newspaper=The New Statesman |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062706/https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/staggers/2016/07/sending-boris-johnson-foreign-office-bad-britain-good-theresa-may |dead-url=no }}</ref>这项任命将确保约翰逊经常出国访问，不能组织反叛联盟，同时也迫使他对从欧盟退出所引起的任何问题承担责任。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.spiegel.de/politik/ausland/boris-johnson-als-britischer-aussenminister-der-muellmann-von-number-10-kommentar-a-1102927.html |title=Boris Johnson als Außenminister: Der Prügelknabe |author=Thomas Hüetlin |language=de |trans-title=Boris Johnson as Foreign Secretary: The whipping boy |newspaper=[[Der_Spiegel|Der Spiegel]] |date=2016-07-14 |accessdate=2016-07-14 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062713/https://www.spiegel.de/politik/ausland/boris-johnson-als-britischer-aussenminister-der-muellmann-von-number-10-kommentar-a-1102927.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NewYorker">{{cite news |url=http://www.newyorker.com/news/john-cassidy/the-huge-challenge-facing-theresa-may |title=The Huge Challenge Facing Theresa May |author=John Cassidy |date=2016-07-13 |accessdate=2016-07-14 |newspaper=New Yorker |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062714/https://www.newyorker.com/news/john-cassidy/the-huge-challenge-facing-theresa-may |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2016年8月，首相梅在国贸大臣福克斯写信给约翰逊说英国贸易不能蓬勃发展，而未来的政策责任仍然在约翰逊的部门后奉劝“失和的大臣们”—约翰逊和[[霍理林|霍理林]]—“不要闹了”。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/08/14/theresa-may-tells-feuding-ministers-to-stop-playing-games-and-ge/|title=Theresa May tells feuding ministers to 'stop playing games' and get on with the job|author=Steven Swinford|work=Daily Telegraph|date=2016-08-14|accessdate=2016-08-16|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062746/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/08/14/theresa-may-tells-feuding-ministers-to-stop-playing-games-and-ge/|dead-url=no}}</ref>约翰逊支持英国变革的录音，被《[[卫报|卫报]]》认为是给梅加快退欧过程施加压力，虽然该文件还记录了前卫生副大臣[[安娜·蘇布里|安娜·蘇布里]]的愤怒，中央政府不能支付“国民医疗服务（NHS）每周3.5亿英镑的”运营成本，她以前将这些言论称为谎言。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/sep/11/boris-johnson-backs-brexit-pressure-campaign-change-britain|title=Boris Johnson backs Brexit pressure campaign Change Britain|author=Peter Walker and Toby Helm|work=Guardian newspapers|date=2016-09-11|accessdate=2016-09-11|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062725/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/sep/11/boris-johnson-backs-brexit-pressure-campaign-change-britain|dead-url=no}}</ref>在一篇《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》批评脱欧派人士的文章中，约翰逊的视频和他对首相缺乏忠诚被称为“浮夸的”。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/what-does-brexit-mean-with-divorce-talks-looming-britain-still-doesnt-have-a-clue/2016/09/16/b2cb7718-79d1-11e6-8064-c1ddc8a724bb_story.html|title=What does Brexit mean? With divorce talks looming, Britain still doesn’t have a clue.|author=Griff Witte|work=Washington Post|date=2016-09-17|accessdate=2016-09-18|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062751/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/what-does-brexit-mean-with-divorce-talks-looming-britain-still-doesnt-have-a-clue/2016/09/16/b2cb7718-79d1-11e6-8064-c1ddc8a724bb_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

约翰逊曾支持[[沙特领导的干预也门行动|沙特阿拉伯对也门的干涉]]，<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/boris-johnson-urged-to-back-probe-into-international-law-violations-during-yemen-war-a7321496.html |title=Boris Johnson urged to back probe into international law violations in Yemen |work=The Independent |date=2016-09-21 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2020-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200827005945/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/boris-johnson-urged-to-back-probe-into-international-law-violations-during-yemen-war-a7321496.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>拒绝阻止英国向沙特阿拉伯出售武器，称沙特阿拉伯在也门战争中没有违反国际人道主义法的明确证据。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/sep/05/mps-to-urge-ban-on-uk-arms-sales-to-saudi-arabia |title=Boris Johnson defends UK arms sales to Saudi Arabia |work=The Guardian |date=2016-09-05 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062748/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/sep/05/mps-to-urge-ban-on-uk-arms-sales-to-saudi-arabia |dead-url=no }}</ref>2016年9月，他被指控阻止联合国调查沙特在也门的战争罪行。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/boris-johnson-yemen-criticised-human-rights-watch-amnesty-international-blocking-war-crimes-inquiry-a7330136.html |title=Boris Johnson criticised by human rights groups after blocking inquiry into war crimes in Yemen |work=The Independent |date=2016-09-27 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062743/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/boris-johnson-yemen-criticised-human-rights-watch-amnesty-international-blocking-war-crimes-inquiry-a7330136.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
