约翰逊作为外交大臣第一次访问土耳其有点紧张，因为在2016年5月，他寫的一首諷刺[[土耳其總統列表|土耳其總統]][[雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安|埃爾多安]]的[[打油詩|打油詩]]在《[[旁觀者|旁觀者]]》舉辦的「冒犯埃爾多安詩歌大賽」中獲勝，得到1000英鎊獎金。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/19/boris-johnson-wins-most-offensive-erdogan-poem-competition |title=Boris Johnson wins 'most offensive Erdoğan poem' competition |trans_title=鲍里斯·约翰逊赢得讽刺埃尔多安诗歌赛 |publisher=The Guardian |date=2016-05-19 |accessdate=2016-07-16 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062749/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/19/boris-johnson-wins-most-offensive-erdogan-poem-competition |dead-url=no }}</ref>一位记者质疑，他是否会为这首公开发表的诗道歉，约翰逊把这个问题当成“琐事一桩”。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2016/09/boris-johnson-refuses-apologise-insulting-president-erdogan/|title=Boris Johnson refuses to apologise for his President Erdogan poem {{!}} Coffee House|date=2016-09-27|newspaper=Coffee House|accessdate=2017-11-15|language=en-US|archive-date=2019-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209035848/https://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2016/09/boris-johnson-refuses-apologise-insulting-president-erdogan/|dead-url=no}}</ref>约翰逊承诺帮助[[土耳其|土耳其]]以“任何可能的方式”加入[[欧盟|欧盟]]，并表示英国继续支持土耳其的民选政府。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.politico.eu/article/boris-johnson-uk-will-help-turkey-join-the-eu/ |title=Boris Johnson: UK will help Turkey join the EU |work=Politico |date=2016-09-28 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062810/https://www.politico.eu/article/boris-johnson-uk-will-help-turkey-join-the-eu/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
在与澳大利亚外交部长[[朱莉·毕晓普|朱莉·毕晓普]]于2016年9月下旬会晤后，约翰逊重申支持谈判增加英国和澳大利亚之间的签证，宣称澳大利亚人去英国比去斯洛伐克等欧洲国家更难以解决是“奇怪”的。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/foreign-affairs/julie-bishop-hopes-for-britainaustralia-exchanges-in-postbrexit-deal/news-story/29d2dd7960c18ab7da8176330d9595cb |title=Julie Bishop hopes for Britain-Australia exchanges in post-Brexit deal |work=The Australian |date=2016-09-23}}</ref>在2017年1月，前政府大臣{{le|威廉·华莱士 (英国)|William Wallace, Baron Wallace of Saltaire|威廉·华莱士}}说，约翰逊在脱欧过程的表现使[[英国公务员服务|公务员]]“绝望”，他“疏远其他欧盟成员国的外长们”。[[英国外交部|外交部]]对此为约翰逊作了辩护。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-latest-news-lord-wallace-salitaire-boris-johnson-foreign-office-despiar-civil-servant-a7509181.html|title=Brexit: Former government member says Foreign Office ‘in despair’ over Boris Johnson|last1=Baxter|first1=Holly|last2=Watts|first2=Joe|date=2017-01-04|work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|accessdate=2017-01-04|archive-date=2020-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605161416/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-latest-news-lord-wallace-salitaire-boris-johnson-foreign-office-despiar-civil-servant-a7509181.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2016年12月，在[[罗马|罗马]]的[[地中海对话|地中海对话]]会议上，约翰逊说：“有些政治家正在扭曲和滥用宗教信仰和不同宗教的差异，以便进一步实现自己的政治目标。这是整个地区最大的政治问题之一……这就是为什么你发现[[沙特阿拉伯|沙特阿拉伯]]、[[伊朗|伊朗]]、每个人，操控傀儡玩[[代理人战争|代理人战争]]。”<ref name="bbc.co.uk">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-38245902|title=Johnson accuses Saudis over 'proxy wars'|date=2016-12-08|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=2018-07-13|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062825/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-38245902|dead-url=no}}</ref>这些意见被解释为英国的外交失误，<ref name="bbc.co.uk"/>因为沙特阿拉伯是英国的盟友，也是英国武器的最大买主。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/industry/defence/11455304/Charted-the-worlds-biggest-arms-importers.html|title=Charted: the world's biggest arms importers|last=Tovey|first=Alan|date=2015-03-08|accessdate=2017-11-15|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062829/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/industry/defence/11455304/Charted-the-worlds-biggest-arms-importers.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/12/08/boris-johnson-theresa-may-odds-pm-rebukes-foreign-secretary/|title=Row over Saudi Arabia comments blows open rift between Theresa May and Boris Johnson|last=Dominiczak|first=Peter|date=2016-12-08|newspaper=The Telegraph|accessdate=2017-11-15|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062836/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/12/08/boris-johnson-theresa-may-odds-pm-rebukes-foreign-secretary/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

首相[[特蕾莎·梅|特蕾莎·梅]]表示，外交大臣的意见并不代表政府的看法。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-38248316|title=Johnson's Saudi comments 'not UK's view'|date=2016-12-08|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=2018-07-13|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062847/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-38248316|dead-url=no}}</ref>其他保守党人却为约翰逊辩护。[[苏格兰保守党|苏格兰保守党]]领袖[[露丝·戴维森|露丝·戴维森]]说：“我认为鲍里斯·约翰逊对于代理人战争和伊朗方面的看法绝对正确。我同意他的分析。现在这可能不是英国政府的立场，但猜猜看，我未在中央政府任职，我认为他是对的。”那个月晚些时候，约翰逊访问了[[巴林|巴林]]，会见了沙特阿拉伯领导人，并对沙特阿拉伯表示赞赏，称沙特在也门是“确保自己不受[[胡塞武装|胡塞武装]]轰炸”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/pa/article-4015600/Boris-Johnson-visit-Middle-East-Saudi-Arabia-proxy-wars-comments.html|title=Boris Johnson charms Gulf leaders days after Saudi Arabia 'proxy wa...|publisher=|accessdate=2017-04-24|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062845/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/pa/article-4015600/Boris-Johnson-visit-Middle-East-Saudi-Arabia-proxy-wars-comments.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
