}</ref>保守党年会召开前夕，约翰逊在第二次演讲中阐述了自己的脱欧方案，这甚至比内阁的还要早。露丝·戴维森呼吁以“更认真的人”取代约翰逊，批评了他的过度乐观主义，并预言英国在过渡时期之后“仍会像现在一样缺乏方向感”。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/boris-johnson-under-fire-from-ruth-davidson-on-eve-of-tory-conference-tdbtgk97c|title=Boris Johnson under fire from Ruth Davidson on eve of Tory conference|last=Hamish Macdonnell|first=Francis Elliott, Political Editor {{!}} Sam Coates {{!}}|date=2017-09-30|newspaper=The Times|accessdate=2017-11-15|issn=0140-0460|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062931/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/boris-johnson-under-fire-from-ruth-davidson-on-eve-of-tory-conference-tdbtgk97c|dead-url=no}}</ref>

约翰逊多次引起争议。2017年1月21日他访问仰光佛教圣地[[仰光大金寺|大金塔]]时，随口吟诵了一段英国作家[[魯德亞德·吉卜林|吉卜林]]在缅甸写下的诗句《[http://www.kiplingsociety.co.uk/poems_mandalay.htm 曼德勒之路]{{Wayback|url=http://www.kiplingsociety.co.uk/poems_mandalay.htm |date=20210206062935 }}》。吉卜林生于英属时期的印度，成长于英国如日中天之时，其作品一直带有为美化殖民主义的色彩。约翰逊吟诵的《曼德勒之路》不仅赞美了英国的士兵，还带有贬损缅甸[[佛教|佛教]]的词句。约翰逊的吟诵被身边的英国驻缅甸大使打断，大使提醒他有电视台在拍摄他的访问新闻，他的身上还佩戴着麦克风，在大金塔里诵读这段诗句“不合适。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2017-09-30/ambassador-stops-boris-johnson-quoting-colonial-poem-in-burmese-temple/|title=Ambassador stops Boris Johnson 'reciting colonial poem' in Burmese temple|newspaper=ITV News|accessdate=2017-11-15|language=en|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062940/https://www.itv.com/news/2017-09-30/ambassador-stops-boris-johnson-quoting-colonial-poem-in-burmese-temple|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson-caught-on-camera-quoting-kipling-poem-in-burmese-temple-a3647431.html|title=Boris Johnson 'caught on camera quoting Kipling in Burmese temple'|newspaper=Evening Standard|accessdate=2017-11-15|language=en-GB|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062945/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson-caught-on-camera-quoting-kipling-poem-in-burmese-temple-a3647431.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/sep/30/boris-johnson-caught-on-camera-reciting-kipling-in-myanmar-temple|title=Boris Johnson caught on camera reciting Kipling in Myanmar temple|last=Booth|first=Robert|date=2017-09-29|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=2017-11-15|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062951/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/sep/30/boris-johnson-caught-on-camera-reciting-kipling-in-myanmar-temple|dead-url=no}}</ref>
