== 政治观点 ==
[[File:Johnson_meets_with_Junker_in_Luxembourg.jpg|thumb]]會面，討論脫歐協議]]
在意识形态上，约翰逊将自己描述为“[[一国保守主义|一国保守主义]]者”。<ref>{{cite news |last=Brogan |first=Benedict |date=2010-04-29 |title=Boris Johnson interview: My advice to David Cameron? I've made savings, so can you |work=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/election-2010/7653636/Boris-Johnson-interview-My-advice-to-David-Cameron-Ive-made-savings-so-can-you.html |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063442/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/election-2010/7653636/Boris-Johnson-interview-My-advice-to-David-Cameron-Ive-made-savings-so-can-you.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Parker |first=George |title=Boris Johnson aims to win back voters as 'One Nation Tory' |work=Financial Times |location=London |date=2014-12-21 |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/74339ea2-88f8-11e4-ad5b-00144feabdc0.html |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2014-12-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227102152/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/74339ea2-88f8-11e4-ad5b-00144feabdc0.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[伦敦政治经济学院|伦敦政治经济学院]]的学者托尼·特拉弗斯描述约翰逊是“相当经典的、即小政府主义、轻度欧洲怀疑主义的保守派。他也欣然接受特拉弗斯赞赏的卡梅伦和[[乔治·奥斯本|乔治·奥斯本]]的“现代社会自由主义”。<ref name="Channel4">{{cite news |title=Boris Johnson: classic Tory or political maverick? |work=Channel 4 News |date=2012-10-09 |url=http://www.channel4.com/news/borish-johnson-classic-tory-or-political-maverick |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2015-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150318042522/https://www.channel4.com/news/borish-johnson-classic-tory-or-political-maverick |dead-url=no }}</ref>《卫报》同意约翰逊在市长期间混合了经济和社会自由主义，<ref>{{cite news |title=Mayor Boris, the liberal |work=The Guardian |location=London |author=Hill, Dave |date=2008-12-04 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/dec/04/boris-johnson-london-mayor-conservatives |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2018-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111063703/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/dec/04/boris-johnson-london-mayor-conservatives |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[经济学人|经济学人]]》声称，约翰逊这样做“超越了他的保守党身份”，并采取更自由主义的立场。<ref>{{cite news |title=Generation Boris |work=The Economist |location=London |date=2013-06-01 |url=http://www.economist.com/news/britain/21578666-britains-youth-are-not-just-more-liberal-their-elders-they-are-also-more-liberal-any |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2018-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180327022525/https://www.economist.com/news/britain/21578666-britains-youth-are-not-just-more-liberal-their-elders-they-are-also-more-liberal-any |dead-url=no }}</ref>约翰逊《旁观者》的同事斯图尔特·里德（Stuart Reid）将后者的观点描述为“社会自由主义的自由意志主义者”观点。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=136}}约翰逊通过对“现有规则典章的热爱并认识到[[社会阶层|社会层次]]结构的必然性”，保留了其个性中的“保守党要素”。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=342}}

{{Quote box|width=25em|align=left|quote=“我是支持自由市场的、宽容的和广义上的自由意志主义者（虽然也许不是极端自由意志主义者）、倾向于看到传统的优点、反政府监管、亲移民、自立自强、爱好酒、爱好狩猎、爱好驾驶和准备捍卫[[格伦·霍德尔|格伦·霍德尔]]的宗教信仰自由。”|author=鲍里斯·约翰逊{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=225}} }}

民间社团“民主审计”的执行主任斯图尔特·威尔克斯-希格指出，“鲍里斯在政治上是灵活的”，<ref name="Channel4"/> 而传记作家索尼娅·普内尔（Sonia Purnell）则表示约翰逊经常改变他对政治问题的看法，反映出她认为的“坚定的保守党外表下的意识形态空虚”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=2}}她后来提到约翰逊的“机会主义，一些人称之为实用主义的政治方法”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=121}}前大伦敦市长肯·利文斯通在接受《新政治家》采访时声称，他曾经担心约翰逊是“[[撒切尔夫人|撒切尔夫人]]以来最强硬的右翼政客”，但通过观察约翰逊的市长任期，他得出结论，约翰逊是“相当懒惰的废物（tosser），只是想忝居高位”，而实绩了了。<ref>{{cite news |title=Ken Livingstone: "Boris is a lazy tosser who just wants to be there" |author=Eaton, George |date=2014-04-30 |work=New Statesman |location=London |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/2014/04/ken-livingstone-boris-lazy-tosser-who-just-wants-be-there |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063509/https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/2014/04/ken-livingstone-boris-lazy-tosser-who-just-wants-be-there |dead-url=no }}</ref>约翰逊有时被描述为“[[民粹主义|民粹主义者]]”<ref>{{cite news |publisher=[[NPR|NPR]] |url=http://www.npr.org/sections/parallels/2016/05/03/476514926/londons-popular-and-populist-mayor-makes-the-case-for-leaving-the-eu |title=London's Popular And Populist Mayor Makes The Case For Leaving The EU |date=2016-05-03 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063512/https://www.npr.org/sections/parallels/2016/05/03/476514926/londons-popular-and-populist-mayor-makes-the-case-for-leaving-the-eu |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://next.ft.com/content/426102ac-230c-11e6-9d4d-c11776a5124d |title=Brussels casts Boris Johnson in populist 'horror scenario' |work=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]] |date=2016-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/01/world/europe/boris-johnson-brexit-conservatives.html |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |title=Luck Runs Out for a Leader of 'Brexit' Campaign |date=2016-06-30 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2019-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022231110/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/01/world/europe/boris-johnson-brexit-conservatives.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>和“[[民族主义|民族主义者]]”。但约翰逊则回应说如果“民族主义”意味着鄙视其他民族的文化那他不是民族主义者。<ref>{{cite web |work=[[Politico|Politico]] |url=http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2016/06/nationalism-donald-trump-boris-johnson-brexit-foreign-policy-xenophobia-isolationism-213995 |title=Why the new nationalists are taking over |date=2016-06-28 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2019-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723081717/https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2016/06/nationalism-donald-trump-boris-johnson-brexit-foreign-policy-xenophobia-isolationism-213995 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

虽然约翰逊因为他在《每日电讯报》中强烈的疑欧论文章而广为人知，但他的许多同事认为这是一种机会主义的诡计，在2016年英国脱欧公投之前，约翰逊曾就加入哪一派犹豫了很长时间，为此他前往乡下别墅，闭关静思，有人提出他可能同情[[联邦欧洲|联邦欧洲]]的事业。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|pp=121–122}}例如，2012年，他欢迎土耳其加入欧盟。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=7}}索尼娅·普内尔说他“既不是真欧洲主义者也不是{{le|小英格兰主义者|Little Englander}}”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=122}}

普内尔同时指出，约翰逊“不是精英主义者”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=52}}在一篇题为《长寿的精英主义》的文章中，约翰逊说“精英和精英主义者不可能一直在他们的洞穴里。”{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=198}}普内尔认为，约翰逊受他左翼的母亲家族的影响，导致他发自内心的“厌恶种族主义”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=25}}

== 公众形象 ==
[[File:Boris_Johnson_hartismere.jpg|thumb]]（中）示威反对关闭医院]]
除了世人皆知的“鲍里斯”，约翰逊还有各种绰号，包括“BoJo”，{{sfnm|1a1=Edwards|1a2=Isaby|1y=2008|1p=43|2a1=Purnell|2y=2011|2p=1}}他的姓和名的[[混成词|混成词]]。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/200709060012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071205171926/http://www.newstatesman.com/200709060012 |title=The BoJo, Ken and Bri show |work=New Statesman |location=London |date=2007-09-06 |accessdate=2010-07-07 |archivedate=2007-12-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>传记作家索尼娅·普内尔将他的公众形象描述为“鲍里斯牌”，指出他在[[牛津大学|牛津大学]]时就已经开始经营了。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=91}}约翰逊的前主编马克斯·黑斯廷斯把这个公众形象称为“外观类似于漫画家[[佩勒姆·格伦维尔·伍德豪斯|佩勒姆·格伦维尔·伍德豪斯]]笔下的人物，富有智慧、魅力、辉煌而令人惊叹的不稳定闪耀”，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=103}}政治科学家安德鲁·克林斯说，约翰逊创造了“有强大智力资本的被喜欢和受信任的个人形象”。{{sfn|Crines|2013|p=1}}[[私家侦探|私家侦探]]编辑{{le|伊恩·希斯洛普|Ian Hislop}}将他定义为“儿童漫画鲍里斯”（Beano Boris），因为他的滑稽的性质，并说：“他是我们的[[贝卢斯科尼|贝卢斯科尼]]……他是我国唯一的对未来的持有乐观态度的政治家，其他人太忙了不能担负这个责任。”<ref name=Huffpo1e4>{{cite news |last1=Frost |first1=Caroline |title=17 Things We Now Know About Boris Johnson, And His Worthiness, Or Not, To Be PM... |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/04/06/boris-johnson-tv-review-irresistible-rise_n_2949591.html |accessdate=2016-01-29 |work=[[The_Huffington_Post|The Huffington Post]] |date=2013-04-03 |archive-date=2018-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211055225/https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/04/06/boris-johnson-tv-review-irresistible-rise_n_2949591.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>对记者戴夫·希尔来说，约翰逊是“英国政治中独一无二的人物，是喜剧演员、骗子、人为颠覆性情景表演者和民粹主义媒体明星前所未有的混合体”。{{sfn|Hill|2016|p=31}}

约翰逊有目的地培养了一种“半散漫的外表”，{{sfn|Edwards|Isaby|2008|p=74}}例如当他公开露面之前，他会刻意让他的头发呈现出散乱的外观。{{sfnm|1a1=Edwards|1a2=Isaby|1y=2008|1p=74|2a1=Purnell|2y=2011|2p=1|3a1=Gimson|3y=2012|3p=301}}普内尔把他描述为“狂热的自我推销者”，他的生活充满了“有趣和笑话”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=3}} 安德鲁·克林斯称为“小丑”，{{sfn|Crines|2013|p=1}}约翰逊说，“幽默是一种工具，你可以用来给药丸加上糖衣（美化讨厌的东西），并得到你想要的重点。”{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=3}}普内尔指出，同事们经常表示，约翰逊利用别人使自己受益，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=183}}传记作家安德鲁·金森注意到约翰逊是“我们时代的伟大奉承者之一”。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=x}}普内尔指出，他使用“一点幽默和一大堆虚张声势”转移了人们对严肃问题的关注点。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=214}}金森的文章称约翰逊是“人道的人”，当维护他自己的利益时，“也可能令人震惊地蔑视别人”。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=108}} 金森还指出，约翰逊“过分渴望被喜欢”。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=258}}

根据普内尔的文章，“约翰逊有着巨大的魅力、机智幽默、充满性张力还有一头金发；他也受到数百万人的认可和喜爱，尽管很多人不得不与他密切合作（更不用说依赖他）。凭着资源、狡猾和战略眼光，当有利时机恰巧与其个人优势相吻合，他就可以摆脱严重的政治变故，但这些手段很少取得到实际成果、甚至详细计划支持”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=456}}此外，普内尔指出，约翰逊是对自己的私生活“高度回避的人”，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=1}}他和别人之间有明显的距离，几乎没有亲密的私人朋友。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=15}}在朋友和家人中，约翰逊被称为“亚力克”而不是“鲍里斯”。{{sfnm|1a1=Edwards|1a2=Isaby|1y=2008|1p=43|2a1=Purnell|2y=2011|2p=1|3a1=Gimson|3y=2012|3p=xiii}}金森说，约翰逊“有很差的礼貌，他常迟到，也不在乎迟到，不关心着装。”{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=301}}高度雄心勃勃，非常有竞争力，生来就是“为争取至高无上而奋斗”。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=17}}他会特别愤怒于他认为侮辱他的个人生活的内容；例如，当《电讯报》中的一篇文章激怒他时，他通过电子邮件给编辑{{le|萨姆·利思|Sam Leith}}传达了简单的信息“滚去死”（Fuck off and die）。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|pp=6–7}}因此，普内尔指出，约翰逊“用笨拙、自嘲或幽默”掩盖了他的无情，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=26}}还补充说，约翰逊是“年少轻狂的讽刺和粗暴性引用”的粉丝。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=37}}

约翰逊能讲流利的[[法语|法语]]和[[意大利语|意大利语]]，[[德语|德语]]和[[西班牙语|西班牙语]]也很出色，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=109}}尤精熟[[拉丁语|拉丁语]]，<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.economist.com/news/britain/21565992-mayor-has-new-plans-london-schools-not-everyone-board-lessons-boris |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113014845/http://www.economist.com/news/britain/21565992-mayor-has-new-plans-london-schools-not-everyone-board-lessons-boris |title=London's schools: The lessons of Boris |work=The Economist |location=London |date=2012-11-10 |accessdate=2012-12-25 |archivedate=2012-11-13 |dead-url=no }}</ref>经常在他的报纸专栏和演讲中引用拉丁语格言。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=91}}

约翰逊说过去他“经常吸[[大麻|大麻]]”，<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/1446705.boris_i_took_cocaine_and_cannabis/ |title=Boris: I took cocaine and cannabis |newspaper=Oxford Mail |date=2007-06-04 |accessdate=2012-10-08 |archive-date=2018-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211033057/https://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/1446705.boris_i_took_cocaine_and_cannabis/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>他赞成使医用大麻合法化。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1902743/Boris-Johnson-Legalise-cannabis-for-pain-relief.html |title=Boris Johnson: Legalise cannabis for pain relief |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=2008-04-24 |accessdate=2012-10-08 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063629/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1902743/Boris-Johnson-Legalise-cannabis-for-pain-relief.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

{{Quote box|width=25em|align=right|quote=“鲍里斯是规则的例外、刻板印象的反面，他具有高度原创性。体态丰腴还有些傻气，与美女海报截然相反。他类似于人们的洗衣筐，堆积起来却常常忘记清洗。”|author=传记作家 索尼娅·普内尔|source={{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=2}} }}

约翰逊在英国政治和新闻业中是一位有争议的人物。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Olson|first1=Donald|title=London for Dummies|date=2010|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|page=21|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vrayaSsuQbUC&pg=PA21|accessdate=2016-02-21|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063627/https://books.google.com/books?id=vrayaSsuQbUC&pg=PA21|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Stone |first=Madeline |title=21 of the most absurd photos of London mayor Boris Johnson |url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/absurd-photos-london-mayor-boris-johnson-2015-11?r=US&IR=T |accessdate=2016-02-21 |work=Business Insider UK |date=2015-11-04 |archive-date=2018-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004120655/http://uk.businessinsider.com/absurd-photos-london-mayor-boris-johnson-2015-11?r=US&IR=T |dead-url=no }}</ref>普内尔将约翰逊描述为“后布莱尔时代英国政治中最为非常规，但引人注目的政治家”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=1}}她补充说，在英国，他“受到百万人的喜爱和所有人的熟知”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=1}}吉尔斯·爱德华兹和乔纳森·伊萨比评论说，约翰逊被称为“广泛而典型的公众人物”，{{sfn|Edwards|Isaby|2008|p=47}}他的朋友将他描述为“讨人喜的保守党人”，可以吸引其他保守党政客不能吸引的选民。<ref>{{cite news |last=Kirkup |first=James |title=Boris Johnson goes looking for Conservative friends in the north |website=The Telegraph |date=2015-01-07 |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2015/11329569/Boris-Johnson-goes-looking-for-Conservative-friends-in-the-north.html |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063606/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2015/11329569/Boris-Johnson-goes-looking-for-Conservative-friends-in-the-north.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>金森表示“人们爱他，因为他让他们笑”，指出他已经成为“保守党普通党员的宠儿”。{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=148}}

普尼尔认识到，在2008年市长选举期间，他将“意见极端化”，{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=345}}批评者认为他是“邪恶、小丑、种族主义和偏执狂”。{{sfn|Purnell|2011|p=365}}《卫报》记者波莉·汤因比的文章把他称为“小丑、花花公子、专注的反社会者和连续行骗的骗子”，{{sfn|Gimson|2012|p=279}}而工党籍前大臣{{le|黑索尔·布莱尔斯|Hazel Blears}}称他为“令人讨厌的右翼精英，有恶劣的意见和犯罪的朋友”。{{sfn|Edwards|Isaby|2008|p=110}}约翰逊也被与美国总统[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]比较。<ref>{{cite news |work=[[Politico|Politico]] |date=2016-05-24 |url=http://www.politico.eu/article/donald-trump-boris-johnson-kiss-mural-brexit-referendum-leave-remain/ |title=Donald Trump and Boris Johnson kiss and make Out |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063613/https://www.politico.eu/article/donald-trump-boris-johnson-kiss-mural-brexit-referendum-leave-remain/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/greenslade/2016/jun/29/new-york-post-compares-boris-johnson-to-donald-trump |date=2016-06-29 |title=New York Post compares Boris Johnson to Donald Trump |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063615/https://www.theguardian.com/media/greenslade/2016/jun/29/new-york-post-compares-boris-johnson-to-donald-trump |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |work=[[Newsweek|Newsweek]] |url=http://www.newsweek.com/boris-johnson-donald-trump-eu-brexit-439957 |title=London mayor Boris Johnson eyes Trump-style insurgency in EU battle |date=2016-03-23 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063620/https://www.newsweek.com/boris-johnson-donald-trump-eu-brexit-439957 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2016年6月，前[[英国副首相|副首相]][[尼克·克莱格|尼克·克莱格]]将他描述为“唐纳德·特朗普的词典同义词”，<ref>{{cite news |last=Wright |first=Oliver |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/eu-referendum-boris-johnson-is-like-donald-trump-with-a-thesaurus-claims-nick-clegg-a7062651.html |title=EU referendum: Boris Johnson is like Donald Trump 'with a thesaurus', claims Nick Clegg |work=The Independent |location=London |date=2016-06-02 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2020-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200824124354/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/eu-referendum-boris-johnson-is-like-donald-trump-with-a-thesaurus-claims-nick-clegg-a7062651.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>保守党国会议员、前[[英国财政大臣|财政大臣]][[祁淦禮|祁淦禮]]将他描述为“更友善的唐纳德·特朗普”，<ref>{{cite news |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/05/30/ken-clarke-boris-johnson-is-just-a-nicer-donald-trump/ |date=2016-05-30 |title=Ken Clarke: Boris Johnson is just a 'nicer Donald Trump' |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063632/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/05/30/ken-clarke-boris-johnson-is-just-a-nicer-donald-trump/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>而[[欧洲委员会|欧洲委员会]]主席办公室主任{{le|马丁·塞勒迈尔|Martin Selmayr}}则将约翰逊和特朗普潜在当选的可能描述为其各自国家的“恐怖情景”。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.politico.eu/article/martin-selmayrs-populist-horror-scenario-trump-le-pen-johnson-grillo/ |work=[[Politico|Politico]] |title=Martin Selmayr's populist 'horror scenario': Trump, Le Pen, Johnson, Grillo |date=2016-05-26 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063637/https://www.politico.eu/article/martin-selmayrs-populist-horror-scenario-trump-le-pen-johnson-grillo/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>然而，约翰逊选择远离特朗普，在许多场合批评他，并且在北約峰會和北約數國領袖一起嘲笑特朗普。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson/12200562/Boris-Johnson-I-was-mistaken-for-Donald-Trump.html |title=Boris Johnson: 'I was mistaken for Donald Trump' |date=2016-03-21 |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063642/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson/12200562/Boris-Johnson-I-was-mistaken-for-Donald-Trump.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |publisher=[[CNBC|CNBC]] |date=2016-06-05 |url=http://www.cnbc.com/2016/06/04/trumps-muslim-comments-extraordinary-ex-london-mayor-boris-johnson.html |title=Trump's Muslim comments 'extraordinary': Ex London mayor Boris Johnson |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063646/https://www.cnbc.com/2016/06/04/trumps-muslim-comments-extraordinary-ex-london-mayor-boris-johnson.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 私人生活 ==
[[File:Boris_Johnson_Leo_Johnson.jpg|thumb]]
约翰逊的父亲[[斯坦利·约翰逊_(作家)|斯坦利·約翰遜]]（Stanley Patrick Johnson，1940年8月18日-）也曾任英国国会议员，1984年落选，约翰逊的母亲[[夏洛特·约翰逊·沃尔|夏洛特·约翰逊·沃尔]]（Charlotte Johnson Wahl，1942年5月29日-）是欧洲人权委员会主席[[詹姆斯·福西特|詹姆斯·福西特]]爵士（James Fawcett，1913年4月26日-1991年6月24日）<ref>Clapham, Andrew (1993). "Human Rights in the Private Sphere". [[OUP|OUP]]. p. 186.</ref>的女儿<ref name=newstates>{{cite news |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/200803270025 |title=Who is Boris Johnson? |work=New Statesman |author=Byrnes, Sholto |date=2008-03-27 |location=London |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080403131250/http://www.newstatesman.com/200803270025 |archivedate=2008-04-03 |accessdate=2017-04-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。约翰逊的妹妹蕾切尔（Rachel Johnson，1965年9月3日-）是记者，三弟利奧是会计公司[[普华永道|普华永道]]的合伙人，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukmediacentre.pwc.com/Media-Library/Leo-Johnson-partner-PwC-Sustainability-and-Climate-Change-566.aspx |title=Leo Johnson, partner, PwC Sustainability and Climate Change |publisher=PricewaterhouseCoopers |date=2009-01-15 |accessdate=2013-05-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100322203724/http://www.ukmediacentre.pwc.com/Media-Library/Leo-Johnson-partner-PwC-Sustainability-and-Climate-Change-566.aspx |archivedate=2010-03-22 }}</ref>四弟[[约·约翰逊|约·约翰逊]]是前下議院议员，官至{{le|商务部副大臣|Department for Business, Innovation and Skills}}，卻因與兄政見不合而離開了政府，卻後又獲其安排為上議院貴族。约翰逊的继父是美国学者{{le|尼古拉斯·沃尔|Nicholas Wahl}}。约翰逊的继母珍妮弗（Jennifer Kidd）是前[[马莎百货|马莎百货]]主席{{le|泰迪·谢夫|Joseph Sieff}}的继女。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/theguardian/2008/may/14/5 |title=People |last=Bates |first=Stephen |work=The Guardian |date=2008-05-14 |location=London |accessdate=2017-04-24 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063701/https://www.theguardian.com/theguardian/2008/may/14/5 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1987年约翰逊与[[阿萊格拉·莫斯廷－歐文|阿萊格拉·莫斯廷－歐文]]（[[Allegra_Mostyn-Owen|Allegra Mostyn-Owen]]，1964年3月22日-）结婚，她是艺术史学家{{le|威廉·莫斯廷－歐文|William Mostyn-Owen}}和意大利作家{{le|盖娅·塞瓦迪奥|Gaia Servadio}}的女儿，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theweek.co.uk/entertainment/17457/boris-johnson%E2%80%99s-first-wife-marries-again|title=Boris Johnson’s first wife marries again|publisher=|accessdate=2017-04-24|archive-date=2016-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517103328/http://www.theweek.co.uk/entertainment/17457/boris-johnson%E2%80%99s-first-wife-marries-again|dead-url=yes}}</ref>1993年离婚。<ref>{{cite news |author=Doward, Jamie |url=http://observer.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,6903,1293085,00.html |title=No dumb blond |work=The Observer |date=2004-08-29 |accessdate=2010-07-07 |location=London |archive-date=2008-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724152524/http://observer.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,6903,1293085,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1993年年底约翰逊与英國律師[[衛雯雅|衛雯雅]]结婚（Marina Wheeler，1964年8月18日-）。<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080413020741/http://www.backboris.com/news/april/Boris_celebrates_Vaisakhi_in_Southall.php |archivedate=2008-04-13 |url=http://www.backboris.com/news/april/Boris_celebrates_Vaisakhi_in_Southall.php |title=Boris celebrates Vaisakhi in Southall |publisher=BackBoris.com |date=2008-04-06 |accessdate=2008-05-03 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>惠勒家族和约翰逊家族已经交往了几十年，<ref name="Gimson">{{Cite book |last=Gimson |first=Andrew |author-link=Andrew Gimson |title=[[Boris:_The_Rise_of_Boris_Johnson|Boris: The Rise of Boris Johnson]] |publisher=Pocket Books [Simon & Schuster] |year=2006 |origyear=2007 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/borisriseofboris00gimsrich/page/11 11]–12, 26–27, 71, 118, 119, 254 |isbn=0-7432-7584-5}}</ref>瑪麗娜·惠勒在布鲁塞尔的欧洲学校和约翰逊同时就读。他们有四个孩子：二個女拉拉和卡西娅，和二個子米洛和西奥多。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/7376621.stm |title=The Boris Johnson story |publisher=BBC News |date=2008-05-04 |accessdate=2008-05-13 |first=Brian |last=Wheeler |archive-date=2008-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080506144031/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/7376621.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>约翰逊和他的家人住在北伦敦的伊斯灵顿。

2009年，约翰逊与艺术顾问海伦·麦金太尔生下一女。2013年，因为这个私生女儿的存在，约翰逊打了一系列的官司，[[英格兰和威尔士上诉法院|上诉法院]]取消了一项禁止要求报告的禁令；法官裁定公众有权知道约翰逊的“鲁莽”行为。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/10070055/Public-has-right-to-know-about-Boris-Johnsons-secret-lovechild-court-rules.html |title=Public has right to know about Boris Johnson's secret lovechild, court rules |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=2013-05-21 |accessdate=2016-03-06 |location=London |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206062132/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/10070055/Public-has-right-to-know-about-Boris-Johnsons-secret-lovechild-court-rules.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Halliday |first=Josh |title=Public has right to know Boris Johnson fathered child during affair, court rules |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/may/21/boris-johnson-fathered-child-affair |accessdate=2016-05-07 |work=The Guardian |date=2013-05-21 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063726/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/may/21/boris-johnson-fathered-child-affair |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pitel |first1=Laura |title='Boris lovechild' can be public knowledge, appeal court rules |url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/law/article3771437.ece |accessdate=2016-05-07 |work=The Times |date=2013-05-22 |location=London |archive-date=2017-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207080311/http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/law/article3771437.ece |dead-url=no }}{{subscription required}}</ref>

2018年9月，鮑裡斯·约翰逊和瑪麗娜·惠勒共同宣布，约翰逊持續被指控婚姻不忠之后，他们“分开了”，还宣布离婚诉讼已经开始。其時約翰遜已與其時婚姻的第三者、現時的太太[[凱莉·西蒙茲|凱莉·西蒙茲]]（Carrie Symonds）同居<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sohu.com/na/331717033_563929?scm=1002.45005a.15d015e0164.PC_NEW_ARTICLE_REC&spm=smpc.content%2Fnew.fd-d.4.1565049600026oXoZw5N |title=唐宁街10号首住未婚情侣 |accessdate=2019-10-19 |archive-date=2021-02-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202214726/https://www.sohu.com/na/331717033_563929?scm=1002.45005a.15d015e0164.PC_NEW_ARTICLE_REC&spm=smpc.content%2Fnew.fd-d.4.1565049600026oXoZw5N |dead-url=no }}</ref>。離婚手續於2020年完成。

約翰遜和西蒙茲两人在2020年3月时都被感染[[2019冠状病毒病|2019冠状病毒病]]，其中西蒙兹还有孕<ref>[https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/coronavirus-now-pregnant-carrie-symonds-has-covid-19-and-pm-boris-johnson-is-still-sick-m6pcpxbjc Coronavirus: Now pregnant Carrie Symonds has Covid-19, and PM Boris Johnson is still sick] {{Wayback|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/coronavirus-now-pregnant-carrie-symonds-has-covid-19-and-pm-boris-johnson-is-still-sick-m6pcpxbjc |date=20210206063755 }}.TheTimes.2020-04-05.[2020-04-07].</ref>。他們的第一个孩子于2020年4月29日，在倫敦大學醫學院附設醫院出生，母子均安<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://udn.com/news/story/6809/4528022 |title=英相強生未婚妻生了 母子均安 |accessdate=2020-04-29 |archive-date=2021-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063814/https://udn.com/news/story/6809/4528022 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=When was Boris Johnson and Carrie Symonds' baby born?|url=https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/11465183/boris-johnson-carrie-symonds-baby-wilfred/|accessdate=2020-05-05|date=2020-05-02|work=The Sun|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206063755/https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/11465183/boris-johnson-carrie-symonds-baby-wilfred/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。两人的儿子名为：韦佛雷德·罗利·尼古拉斯·约翰逊（Wilfred Lawrie Nicholas Johnson），纪念两人的祖父和治療約翰遜的醫生。<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/amp/uk-52513103 “Boris Johnson and Carrie Symonds name baby son Wilfred Lawrie Nicholas”] {{Wayback|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/amp/uk-52513103 |date=20200503170724 }} BBC [02-05-2020]</ref>二人2021年5月29日在[[西敏寺|西敏寺]]低調成婚<ref>{{cite news |title=约翰逊秘密结婚 首相办公室证实婚讯 |url=https://www.dw.com/zh/%E7%BA%A6%E7%BF%B0%E9%80%8A%E7%A7%98%E5%AF%86%E7%BB%93%E5%A9%9A-%E9%A6%96%E7%9B%B8%E5%8A%9E%E5%85%AC%E5%AE%A4%E8%AF%81%E5%AE%9E%E5%A9%9A%E8%AE%AF/a-57718000 |accessdate=2021-05-30 |archive-date=2021-05-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210531075458/https://www.dw.com/zh/%E7%BA%A6%E7%BF%B0%E9%80%8A%E7%A7%98%E5%AF%86%E7%BB%93%E5%A9%9A-%E9%A6%96%E7%9B%B8%E5%8A%9E%E5%85%AC%E5%AE%A4%E8%AF%81%E5%AE%9E%E5%A9%9A%E8%AE%AF/a-57718000 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 公民权 ===

